Bank of Japan (8301)  Governor Masaaki Shirakawa will meet Finance Minister Taro Aso and Economy
Minister Akira Amari today in  Tokyo , according to people
familiar with the meeting.  The people spoke on condition of anonymity because the
meeting is private. They did not say what would be discussed.  The Mainichi newspaper reported today that the three will
discuss an accord between the government and the central bank.  Prime Minister Shinzo Abeâ€™s administration anticipates the
BOJ will adopt a 2 percent target for inflation at its Jan.
21-22 gathering, Vice-Finance Minister Shunichi Yamaguchi said
